.TH HSH 1 "December 2024" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple shell (command interpreter)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple command line interpreter that executes commands read from standard input.
.PP
When
.B hsh
is invoked, it displays a prompt and waits for user input. After reading a command line, it attempts to execute the command.
.SH USAGE
.PP
Commands can be executed in two ways:
.PP
.B Interactive mode:
.RS
$ ./hsh
.br
$ /bin/ls
.br
$ exit
.RE
.PP
.B Non-interactive mode:
.RS
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.RE
.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell
.TP
.B env
Print environment variables
.SH FILES
No configuration files are used.
.SH AUTHORS
See AUTHORS file in the repository.
.SH BUGS
Probably has some bugs. Still learning.
